<br>
1.  I can pull for AoE groups.  This is especially true in HS where the harm touches can be absorbed by my shield (as long as there aren't too many of them)<br>
<br>
2.  I can tank sometimes when necessary in xp situations.  I do this often when duoing with a ranger or rogue.  Rogue can backstab after I nuke, til he builds up enough aggro, then I nuke again.<br>
<br>
3.  High end mobs almost always seem to cast an AoE.  I don't take damage, and can recast it when possible (usually easy to do), thus saving the clerics mana for tanks who need it.<br>
<br>
4.  I can be more aggressive with the nuking in xp groups, especially if we need things dead in a hurry.<br>
<br>
Our epic effect is one of the absolute best out there in my opinion.  I know I am not alone in that thinking as well. <p><img src ="http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/86/2369886.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5>Staff of the Four - Epic Quest</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  